AGI - "The Christian is not bullying. His strength is the power of the Spirit", strong and kind. Thus on his arm Pope Francis in the homily of the Mass of Pentecost. "And not even with calculations and misfortunes, but with the energy that comes from fidelity to truth, that the Spirit teaches to our hearts and makes us grow." "We give ourselves to the Spirit but do not give us the strength of the world. And so - the Pontiff has emphasized - we do not give up, but we continue to talk of peace to those who want the war, to talk of forgiveness to those who sow revenge, to talk of welcome and solidarity to those who land the doors and erect barriers, to talk of life to those who choose death, to talk about respect to those who love to humiliate, insult and discard, to speak empty of fidelity to those who reject every bond, confusing freedom with a superficial individualism, matte. Without letting us be intimidated by the difficulties, neither by the derisions, nor by the oppositions that, today as yesterday, never fail in apostolic life." "And at the same time - Francis added to arm - our announcement wants to be kind, to welcome everyone. Let us not forget this: all, all, all".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"We had the Holy Spirit as a gift in Baptism and Confirmation," the Pope noted. "From the 'story' of this Basilica, like the Apostles, we are invited, today especially, to proclaim the Gospel to all, always going beyond, not only geographically, but also beyond the 'ethnic and religious barriers, for a truly universal mission". "And thanks to the Spirit we can and must do it with the same strength and with the same kindness. With the same force: not with bullying and impositions." The Pontiff also stressed that "without this power of the Spirit we would never succeed in defeating evil," "He enters the heart and heals everything".
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"All of us, brothers and sisters, we need so much hope, which is not optimism, is another thing. Hope is like an anchor on the shore and we with the rope towards hope," Pope Francis added. "We need hope, to raise our eyes on horizons of peace, brotherhood, justice and solidarity. This is the only way of life, there is no other way of life." But we know we're not alone. We have this security: that with the help of the Holy Spirit, with his gifts, we can travel together and make it ever more viable for others," the Pontiff said.&nbsp;

