AGI - One of the most touching moments of Pope Francis' visit (about 9 hours) in Verona, was when on stage of the Arena, during the event "Arena of Peace - Justice and Peace will kiss", the Israeli Maoz Inon, to which Hamas killed his parents on October 7, and the Palestinian Aziz Sarah, to whom the Israeli army killed his brother. After making one by the side of the other, their testimonies, they embraced and then embraced the Pontiff. A long applause departed from the Arena and all (about 12,500) stood up.
"In front of the suffering of these two brothers, which is the suffering of two peoples can not be said anything," Francis said. "They had the courage to embrace themselves. And this is not only courage and witness of wanting peace but also a project of future. To embrace." "Peace will never be the fruit of distrust, the fruit of the walls, of weapons aimed at each other," the Pope said. "Our civilizations are now sowing death, destruction, fear. Seeds, brothers and sisters, hope! We are sowers of hope! Each seeks the way to do it, but sowers of hope, always" and "do not become spectators of the so-called 'invitable' war".
<div </div
&nbsp;
"You, weavers and weavers of dialogue in the Holy Land, please ask world leaders to listen to your voice, to involve you in the negotiating processes, because the agreements arise from reality and not from ideologies," he added. As soon as he arrived in the city of Scala, Francis met in the Basilica of San Zeno priests and consecrated persons.
"If Shakespeare's genius was inspired by the beauty of this place to tell us the tormented events of two lovers, impeded by the hatred of their respective families, we Christians, inspired by the Gospel, let us commit ourselves to sow everywhere a love: where there is hatred, that I put love, where there is hatred that I am able to sow love. A stronger love of hate - today there is so much hatred in the world -, sowing a stronger love of hatred and stronger than death. Dream like this, Verona, like the city of love, not only in literature, but in life." Then, the dialogue with about 7,000 boys and children waiting for him on the church festival. Below is another appointment very heard by the Pope: the meeting and the next lunch with the prisoners of the prison in Montorio.
<div </div
&nbsp;
Here the Pontiff expressed his pain for those who in cell, "in an extreme gesture, they gave up living". "Life is always worthy of being lived, always!", he said inviting not to give in to discouragement: "There is always hope for the future, even when everything seems to turn off. Our existence, that of each of us, is important, we are not waste material."
Last date, the Bentegodi Stadium. Approximately 32 thousand await him among young people, families, associations and parish communities. Francis presided over the eve of Pentecost and pronounced the whole homily on his arm. An homily on the Holy Spirit, "protagonist of our lives", which "opens our hearts", "gives us courage to live Christianly" not to be like so many "Christians who are like warm, warm or cold water". The Holy Spirit, "which makes harmony", whose opposite is war.&nbsp;
